## Summary

Wired the M3 sprint's "deployment surface" half onto the existing M3
foundation: a GitHub Actions smoke gate, a Bearer-token auth
middleware, a deployment runbook, and an SLO document. The
middleware uses `subtle::ConstantTimeEq` for the token comparison and
treats the dev-mode case (no `COGNICODE_MCP_AUTH_TOKEN` set) as an
opt-in escape hatch.

To keep the auth logic testable without the broken
`cognicode-mcp-server` binary build (see Risks #1 below), the
constant-time `check_bearer_token` function was extracted to a new
library module (`crates/cognicode-mcp/src/auth.rs`) exposed via a
new `[lib]` target. The `cognicode-mcp` and `cognicode-mcp-server`
binaries both `use cognicode_mcp::auth::...;` unchanged in spirit.

