### M3.5 — Auth middleware

- [x] Added `subtle = "2.6"` to the workspace `Cargo.toml` deps
  block (with a comment explaining why `subtle` is preferred over
  `if a == b` for secret comparison).
- [x] Added `subtle.workspace = true` to
  `crates/cognicode-mcp/Cargo.toml`.
- [x] Added a new `[lib]` target `cognicode_mcp` exposing the auth
  module. The new `src/lib.rs` and `src/auth.rs` files are
  documented as the public surface; binaries stay private to the
  crate.
- [x] Extracted `pub fn check_bearer_token(header_value: Option<&str>, expected: &str) -> Result<(), StatusCode>`
  to `src/auth.rs`. The function:
  - Accepts the `Authorization` header as a string slice.
  - Strips the `Bearer ` prefix case-insensitively (RFC 7235).
  - Rejects headers ≤ 7 bytes (no token after the scheme).
  - Compares with `subtle::ConstantTimeEq::ct_eq` and branches on
    the `Choice`, NOT on the token contents, to preserve
    constant-time behaviour.
- [x] Added `async fn auth_middleware(...)` in `src/server.rs`. The
  middleware:
  - Reads `COGNICODE_MCP_AUTH_TOKEN` on every request (not cached
    at startup, so an operator can rotate the token by restarting
    the container).
  - On `Err(_)` or `Ok("")` returns `Ok(next.run(request).await)`
    — the dev-mode escape hatch.
  - Otherwise calls `check_bearer_token` and propagates
    `StatusCode::UNAUTHORIZED` on mismatch.
  - Mounted via `middleware::from_fn_with_state(shared_ctx.clone(), auth_middleware)`
    so the `Arc<HandlerContext>` is available (currently unused
    but matches the design's stateful middleware pattern).
- [x] Split the router so the auth layer applies to `/mcp` only:
  ```rust
  let api_routes = Router::new()
      .nest_service("/mcp", service)
      .layer(middleware::from_fn_with_state(shared_ctx.clone(), auth_middleware));
  let public_routes = Router::new()
      .route("/health", get(health_handler))
      .route("/ready", get(ready_handler))
      .route("/metrics", get(metrics_handler));
  let app = Router::new().merge(api_routes).merge(public_routes).with_state(shared_ctx);
  ```
  The exempt list (`/health`, `/ready`, `/metrics`) matches design
  decision #2 in the spec: orchestrator probes and Prometheus
  scrapers do not need a token.
- [x] Added a startup `tracing::info!` line (`Mode C: auth ENABLED`
  / `Mode C: auth DISABLED`) so the security posture is obvious
  in container logs — symmetric with the existing `Mode A/B`
  lines for standalone vs. PG-connected.
- [x] Refactored the inline `|| async { "OK" }` closure for
  `/health` into a named `health_handler() -> &'static str`
  function. This is a no-op behaviour change; it makes the
  router refactor cleaner and gives a stable function pointer
  for future metrics.

